"57:20:4" : {s: 57, a: 20, w: 4, r: "دنو", t: "ٱلدُّنْيَا", l: "دُّنْيَا", lc: 115, tl: "l-dun'yā", lb: "দুনিয়া",e: "(of) the world", b: "দুনিয়া", i: "dunia", f: 115, rm: "To be near, come near or low, let down, be akin to.  Danaa (prf. 3rd. p.m. sing.): He drew near. Yudniina (imp. 3rd. p.f. plu.): They should let down, draw lower. Daanin (act. pic. m. sing.): Near at hand; bending (so) low (as to be within easy reach to pluck). Adnaa (elative.): Nearest; worse; lower; best; more fit; more proper; more likely; more probable; nearer; near; less; fewer. Dunyaa: This world.", ag: "ال التعريف وصفة مرفوع", eg: "Determiner al and Adjective Nominative case", tag: "ADJ", pos: "ADJ", att: "NOM", qual: "", deg: "", gen: "F", num: "S", mood: "", lu: "أَدْنَىٰٓ،دَنَا،دَانٍۢ،دَانِيَةٌۭ"},
